stitution formed through the acquisition of hbos by lloyds tsb in  the groups history stems from the founding in  by the parliament of scotland of the bank of scotland which is the second oldest bank in the united kingdom the groups headquarters is located at  gresham street in the city of london and its registered office is on the mound in edinburgh lloyds banking groups activities are organised into retail banking including mortgages and sole traders commercial life pensions  insurance and wealth  international lloyds has extensive overseas operations in the us europe the middle east and asia following the takeover the group stopped using the name hbos publicly the halifax brand products and pricing were discontinued in scotland until reestablished in  the halifax and lloyds bank brands are used in england and wales and the bank of scotland brand is used in scotland each offering different products and pricing lloyds banking groups ceo antónio hortaosório told the banker we will keep the different brands because the customers are very different in terms of attitude lloyds banking group is listed on the london stock exchange lse and is a constituent of the ftse  index it had a market capitalisation of approximately gb£billion as of  march —the thlargest of any lse company it has a secondary listing on the new york stock exchange where it has a market capitalisation value of us billion contents  history  origins  lloydstsb merger  acquisition of hbos  october  to january   february to june   june  to present  divestment  divisions and subsidiaries  retail  commercial banking  insurance  consumer finance  sponsorships  awards and recognition  controversies  money laundering  tax avoidance  complaints via the financial ombudsman service  sharia account  hbos fraud  references  external links historyedit originsedit for more details on this topic see lloyds bank and hbos lloyds bank was one of the oldest banks in the uk tracing its establishment to taylors and lloyds founded in  in birmingham by button maker john taylor and iron producer and dealer sampson lloyd ii through a series of mergers lloyds became one of the big four banks in the uk bank of scotland which originated in the th century is the secondoldest surviving uk bank after the bank of england in  a wave of consolidations in the uk banking market led the former halifax building society—which originated in —to agree to a £ billion merger with bank of scotland trustee savings bank tsb can trace its roots back to the first savings bank founded by henry duncan in ruthwell dumfriesshire in  tsb itself was created in  by an act of parliament that merged all the remaining savings banks in england  wales as tsb bank plc and in scotland except airdrie savings bank as tsb scotland plc lloydstsb mergeredit park row leeds branch of lloyds bank with a sculpture of the black horse called cancara in the foreground in  lloyds bank merged with tsb forming lloyds tsb group plc in  the group acquired scottish widows a mutual lifeassurance company based in edinburgh in a deal worth £ billion this made the group the secondlargest uk provider of life assurance and pensions after prudential in september the same year lloyds tsb purchased chartered trust from standard chartered bank for £ million to form lloyds tsb asset finance division which provides motor retail and personal finance in the united kingdom under the trading name black horse lloyds tsb continued to take part in the consolidation making a takeover bid for abbey national in  which was later rejected by the competition commission in october  lloyds tsb group agreed on the sale of its subsidiary nbnz holdings limited—comprising the groups new zealand banking and insurance operations—to australia and new zealand banking group in july  lloyds tsb group announced the sale of its business in argentina to banco patagonia sudameris sa and its business in colombia to primer banco del istmo sa on  december  lloyds tsb announced that it had reached an agreement to sell its credit card business goldfish to morgan stanley bank international limited for £ million in  lloyds tsb announced that it had sold its abbey life insurance division to deutsche bank for £ million acquisition of hbosedit head office of the bank of scotland at the mound edinburgh on  september  the bbc reported that hbos was in takeover talks with lloyds tsb in response to a precipitous drop in hboss share price the talks concluded successfully that evening with a proposal to create a banking giant which would hold a third of uk mortgages an announcement was made on  september  on  november  the new acquisition and government preference share purchase was agreed by lloyds tsb shareholders hbos shareholders overwhelming approved the deal on  december lloyds tsb group changed its name to lloyds banking group upon completion of the takeover on  january  on  february  eric daniels the ceo of the group was questioned about the banking crisis during a session of the treasury select committee of the house of commons one of the key issues concerned lloyds takeover of hbos and the amount of due diligence carried out before the acquisition daniels said that a company would always like to do more due diligence on another company but there are legal limits on how much is possible before an actual acquisition losses were slightly more than the £ billion originally identified by the due diligence owing to writeoffs of property loans because of falling property prices and the lack of demand for it the thenchairman of lloyds sir victor blank said in august  that losses had been at the worst end of expectations and that the lloyds board was surprised by the speed at which the losses—which were caused by the unexpectedly sharp contraction of the world economy in late  and early —happened this position was confirmed by archie kane a senior lloyds executive in scotland in evidence to the scottish parliaments economy committee in december  on  february  lloyds banking group said that the losses at hbos were greater than had been anticipated at around £ billion the share price of lloyds banking group fell  on the london stock exchange carrying other bank shares with it october  to january edit see also  united kingdom bank rescue package and  united kingdom bank rescue package the aylesbury branch of lloyds bank formerly the bucks and oxon union bank on  october  prime minister gordon brown announced a government plan for the treasury to invest £ billion us billion € billion of new capital into major uk banks—including royal bank of scotland group lloyds tsb and hbos—to avert a collapse of the financial sector barclays avoided taking a capital investment from the uk government by raising capital privately and hsbc moved capital to its uk business from its other businesses overseas it was later confirmed that lloyds tsb would have been required by the financial services authority fsa to take additional capital from the government if it had not taken over hbos after the recapitalisations and lloyds acquisition of hbos the uk government held a  stake in lloyds banking group february to june edit in february  after it became apparent that the recession would be deeper than originally anticipated the fsa was instructed to stress test the banks against a severe economic downturn the fsa stated that the assumptions underlying the stress test were not intended to be a forecast of what was likely to happen but to simulate a near catastrophic economic scenario these assumptions included a peaktotrough fall in uk gross domestic product gdp of over  with no growth until  and returning to trendrate growth in  a rise in uk unemployment to just over  a  peaktotrough fall in uk house prices a  peaktotrough fall in uk commercial property prices the conclusion from this exercise was that lloyds would need additional capital if such a scenario ever occurred because the wholesale funding markets were effectively closed at the time in march  lloyds made a deal with the uk government consisting of two elements redemption of preference shares the £ billion of preference nonvoting shares held by ukfi were repaid on  june  following the issue of new ordinary shares—this avoided the payment of £ million annual interest to the treasury and allowed lloyds to resume payment of dividends when profits allowed these new ordinary shares were initially available to existing shareholders through an open offer at  pence that closed on  june — were taken up the remaining  were placed in the market on  june  at  pence this open offer and placing was underwritten by the treasury if none of these new ordinary shares had been bought by existing shareholders or the open market the government—as underwriters of the deal—would have bought them and their shareholding would have increased to a maximum of  this did not happen the governments holding remained at  and lloyds became the first european bank to repay government credit crunch investment following the governments  participation in junes open offer the average buying price of the governments total shareholding was  pence asset protection scheme lloyds agreed in principle to enter the governments asset protection scheme to insure it against potential future losses on previous loans—primarily on the old hbos portfolio the fee for this would have been paid for by the issue to the government of new b nonvoting shares which could have increased the government holding to a maximum of c—or higher if the government had bought all the ordinary shares issued to redeem the preference shares june  to presentedit king street manchester branch of lloyds bank designed by charles heathcote in  lloyds impairments peaked in the first half of  by mid the asset protection scheme increasingly looked like a poor deal for lloyds following negotiations the government confirmed on  november  that lloyds would not enter the scheme—although rbs still would instead lloyds launched a rights issue to raise capital from existing shareholders as an existing  shareholder the government chose to take part in this and thus maintained its shareholding at  following this the national audit office calculated the governments average buying price for its entire stake in lloyds to be about  pence it was announced in the governments prebudget report on  december  that the forecast for the total loss to taxpayers for all the bank bailouts had been reduced from £ billion to £ billion—in part because of the restructuring of the governments asset protection scheme the final part of the december  capital raise involved issuing new shares to debt holders in february  this diluted existing shareholders—including the uk government whose shareholding was reduced from  to around  according to the accord trade union general secretary ged nichols lloyds banking group had cut  jobs between february  and august  and in august  it announced another  job losses the group sold its  stake in insurance company esure to esure group holdings on  february  the share was valued at around £ million on  november  it was reported that lloyds was considering selling its  stake in st jamess place wealth management to raise around £ billion in april  lloyds sold its lossmaking spanish retail operation—originally banco halifax hispania—and the local investment management business in spain to banco de sabadell lloyds will receive a  stake in sabadell worth about € million and an additional sum of up to € million over the next five years in september  it was reported that the uk government was planning to sell up to a quarter of its shares in lloyds banking group the government sold  of its shares on  september  at p raising £ billion and reducing its stake to  the uk government then sold a further  on  march  at p raising a further £bn and reducing its stake to  a trading plan of incremental sales during  reduced the publicly owned stake to below  by the end of october sales resumed in november  as the holding was reduced to  on  march  the british government confirmed its remaining shares in lloyds banking group had been sold divestmentedit main article tsb bank united kingdom the edgbaston branch of lloyds bank at five ways birmingham designed by p b chatwin in  the uk governments purchase of a  stake in the group in  was considered as state aid under european commission competition laws the group would be required to sell a portion of its business the groups divestment plan—codenamed verde—identified  branches which would be transferred to a new business customers with accounts held by the branches and staff employed within them would be transferred the new business would be formed from some lloyds tsb branches in england and wales all branches of lloyds tsb scotland plc and cheltenham  gloucester plc these would operate under the tsb brand as tsb bank plc the remainder of the lloyds tsb business would be rebranded as lloyds bank lloyds banking group reached a heads of terms agreement in july  to sell the verde branches to the cooperative bank for £ million the final transfer of tsb bank plc to the new owner was due to be completed by late  in february  it was reported that lloyds banking group were considering a stock market flotation of the tsb business as an alternative should the transfer not be completed on  april  the cooperative bank decided not to proceed with the acquisition because of the economic downturn and the tough regulatory environment imposed on banks lloyds banking group said that the rebranding to tsb bank would still take place and that the new bank will be divested through an initial public offering in  tsb bank began operations on  september  under ceo paul pester lloyds banking group announced that  of tsbs shares would be floated on  june  however with the offer being  times oversubscribed  of tsbs shares were sold at p on  june banco sabadell agreed to purchase tsb in march  and completed the acquisition on  july  the purchase meant lloyds sold its final holding in tsb divisions and subsidiariesedit the group is organised as follows retailedit retail headed up by david oldfield is the face of lloyds banking group on the high street on the phone and online with  million customers in total they are the uks largest retail bank the division focuses on lloyds bank in england and wales and bank of scotland in scotland providing a full range of banking and financial services to some  million personal customers through over  branches across the uk halifax also provides a full range of banking and financial services to some  million personal customers through c branches across england wales scotland and northern ireland lloyds is the largest employer in the metropolitan borough of calderdale west yorkshire where it has its halifax subsidiary headquarters major offices and its central data centre other units include birmingham midshires a mortgage and savings brand and intelligent finance commercial bankingedit this division headed by andrew bester group executive director provides banking and related services for small  mediumsized enterprises smes midmarket companies major uk and multinational corporate and financial institutions lloyds bank commercial banking lloyds securities usa branch corporate banking financial markets capital markets bank of scotland commercial lloyds bank commercial finance insuranceedit the insurance division led by antonio lorenzo group director is one of the uks largest insurers and provides longterm savings protection and investment products and general insurance products to customers in the uk and europe scottish widows is the groups specialist provider of life assurance pensions and investment products distributed through the lloyds banking group branch network through independent financial advisers and directly via the telephone and internet insurance and investments also includes general insurance underwriting and broking home creditor motor travel pet clerical medical – the clerical medical sales team merged with scottish widows in  lloyds bank insurance services limited halifax insurance buildings contents and motor insurance via lloyds bank halifax  bank of scotland branches telephone sales internet rd parties eg moneysupermarketcom scottish widows – offset mortgages consumer financeedit consumer finance led by antónio lorenzo group director is made up of three different businesses asset finance cards and european online deposits asset finance the business is made up of two key brands lex autolease black horse consumer credit cards commercial card and acquiring solutions european onshore banking sponsorshipsedit lloyds banking group is an active supporter of disability rights and best practice it is a gold member of the employers’ forum on disability in  the group helped create and currently sponsors the royal association for disability rights radar radiate network which aims to support and develop a talent pool of people with disabilities and health conditions and to potentially act as a source of thinking for organisations on how disabled talent is best spotted and developed awards and recognitionedit carfax oxford branch of lloyds bank on high street designed by stephen salter in  in july  euromoney announced lloyds tsb as the winners of its awards for excellence in june  lloyds tsb group came top in the race for opportunity’s rfo annual survey in may  lloyds tsb corporate markets was recognised as ‘bank of the year’ for the fifth year running at real fd cbi fds excellence awards in october s what investment magazine awards halifax won best savings account provider and halifax share dealing was also named best share dealing service in october s consumer money awards halifax won best first time mortgage provider lloyds brands were commended in several other categories including cheltenham  gloucester for best remortgage provider and best high street mortgage provider lloyds tsb for best current account provider best student account provider and best customer service provider and halifax for best isa provider and best high street savings provider in november s personal finance awards halifax was awarded best premium current account for the ultimate reward current account and best savings account provider in the best mortgage provider category halifax was highly commended halifax sharedealing was named best online stockbroker for the third year in a row and was highly commended in the excellence in customer service category halifax investments was named best investment product provider lloyds tsb won best student financebanking provider and was also highly commended in the best current account provider awards scottish widows was highly commended in the best pension provider category in november s your mortgage awards halifax won the award for best overall mortgage lender for the eighth year running as well as the award for best large loans mortgage lender birmingham midshires was named best specialist and buytolet mortgage lender and lloyds tsb won the award for best overseas mortgage lender controversiesedit the halifax branch of lloyds bank on george square built  money launderingedit a  report by the wall street journal described how credit suisse barclays lloyds banking group and other banks were involved in helping the alavi foundation bank melli the government of iran and others circumvent us laws banning financial transactions with certain states they did this by stripping information out of wire transfers thereby concealing the source of funds lloyds banking group settled with the us government for us million the us governments manhattan district attorneys office was involved although the case was merged with one at the federal us department of justice  tax avoidanceedit in  a case was brought against lloyds by hm revenue and customs on grounds of tax avoidance lloyds was accused of pouring hundreds of millions of pounds into transatlantic tax avoidance schemes in the form of loans to american financial institutions complaints via the financial ombudsman serviceedit lloyds tsb received  complaints via the financial ombudsman service in the last half of  this when added to the other brands of the lloyds banking group was twice the number of complaints received by barclays—the nextmostcomplainedabout uk bank the financial ombudsman service upheld fewer complaints against lloyds tsb than it did against barclays sharia accountedit lloyds tsb became the first mainstream uk bank to launch a shariacompliant business account the islamic business and corporate account was to be run in line with sharia principles which has resulted in some controversy hbos fraudedit lloyds banking group has been criticised for failing to compensate or even apologise to victims of fraud perpetrated by employees of hbos referencesedit  a b c d e annual report  pdf lloyds banking group retrieved  april    fast facts lloyds banking group plc retrieved  april    antónio hortaosório moves out of his comfort zone the banker april   ftse allshare index ranking stockchallengecouk retrieved  march    lloyds banking group plc ads marketwatch  lloyds bankhistory lloyds tsb archived from the original on  september  retrieved  september    kargupta sudip  september  uk banks prepare for inevitable shakeup reuters retrieved  april    bos and halifax agree merger bbc news  retrieved    tsb bank history lloyds tsb archived from the original on  october  retrieved  september    lloyds bank to merge with tsb new york times  october  retrieved  september    lloyds tsb buys scottish widows bbc news  june  retrieved  september    standard chartered wins bn chase deal the independent  september  retrieved  february    report damns lloyds tsbs bid for abbey national london the telegraph  march  retrieved  september    lloyds tsb confirms possible sale of national bank nz herald  june  retrieved  september    banco hiptecario prospectus page  pdf banco hiptecario  retrieved  september  